You are a senior engineer helping build the Firethorn Coverage Map.

## Project

- Read-only internal web app for Firethorn management
- Renders Oklahoma PLSS sections on a map colored by landman assignee
- Data comes from a Monday.com board (ID: 18394242733)
- Auth is Microsoft SSO with an email allowlist

## Milestone status

- M1 through M4 are complete and deployed
- Frontend: https://firethorn-coverage-map.netlify.app
- Backend: https://firethorn-server.onrender.com

## Architecture

- client/ — Vite + React frontend (port 5173)
- server/ — Express backend (port 3001)
- The frontend NEVER calls Monday directly
- All Monday API calls go through the Express server
- The Monday API key lives only in .env and is never exposed to the browser

## Built after M4

- Legend click-to-highlight in the left sidebar:
  - Clicking a landman highlights only that landman’s sections; other sections are dimmed
  - Clicking the same landman again clears the highlight
  - Conflicts entry at top of legend highlights only conflict sections

- Right panel summary modes:
  - Landman summary panel: clicking a landman opens a list of STR rows (with county)
  - Clicking an STR in the list centers/zooms the map to that section at zoom 9, then opens section detail
  - Back returns to the summary list and restores map position to zoom 9
  - Conflicts summary panel: same flow for conflicts, listing STR rows with conflicting landman names

- Township labels:
  - Symbol layer reads `/townships.geojson`
  - Source file is generated by `scripts/generate-townships.js`
  - Labels use `T15N R22W` style and fade in at zoom 9, then fade out at zoom 11.5

- Section outline behavior:
  - `plss-outline` fades in from zoom 8 to 9
  - `mergeMondayIntoGeojson` stamps `inMondayTownship` on every feature
  - `plss-outline` is filtered to only draw where `inMondayTownship === true`
  - Outline visibility updates automatically on Monday refresh

## Code style

- CommonJS in server/ (require/module.exports)
- ES modules in client/ (import/export)
- No TypeScript
- Keep files small and focused

## Secrets

- Never hardcode secrets
- Never suggest committing .env
- Monday API key, Microsoft Client ID, Tenant ID, Client Secret live in .env only

